Job Title: Systems Engineer - Air Traffic Infrastructure Project
Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond
Ad Text:
Systems Engineer - Air Traffic Infrastructure Project

Daily rate: up to $1,200 per day (flexible for the right candidate)

Location: Sydney

Citizenship: Australian citizenship required (NV1 clearance not essential)

About the Role

Talent International is partnering with a leading avionics client to deliver a major air traffic infrastructure refurbishment program.

This role sits within the technical systems stream of the program and will focus on delivering robust and reliable software and system engineering outcomes that support safe, modern, and efficient air traffic operations.

The ideal candidate will be a strategic problem solver who can connect complex technical and operational elements, communicate effectively across large stakeholder groups, and drive progress even when facing resistance or ambiguity.

What You'll Do

Lead the design, development, testing, and implementation of resilient software and system solutions

Apply systems engineering practices throughout the full SDLC and system lifecycle management

Manage technical stakeholders and vendors to ensure successful delivery across multiple project streams

Prepare and review system design and solution architecture documentation, ensuring alignment with overall strategy and existing initiatives

Provide strong leadership, influencing and guiding outcomes through effective communication and stakeholder engagement

Take ownership of deliverables and operate with autonomy as a senior technical contributor within a high-performing team

What You'll Bring

A degree in Engineering or Information Technology from an Australian tertiary institution (or certified equivalent qualification)

Eligibility for registration as a Professional Engineer (RPEQ) or equivalent

Proven experience applying Systems Engineering principles across design, development, and implementation phases

Extensive experience in software system design, development, testing, and quality/configuration management

Demonstrated strength in stakeholder and vendor management within complex, multi-disciplinary environments

Excellent business writing, documentation, and communication skills

The ability to operate with limited direction, showing initiative and accountability for outcomes

Nice to Have

Experience within air traffic control, aviation systems, or broader aerodrome technology environments will be highly regarded.

Location: Sydney (3 days in office/week)

Design, build and optimise AI-powered solutions across the business using Microsoft Copilot Studio & Azure AI services.
Work closely with data engineers and analytics teams to connect structured data (Snowflake) into intelligent workflows and agents.
Help stand up the business’s AI enablement layer, connecting LLMs to real-world data and business logic.
Build and productionise deep learning models for NLP, recommendation engines, classification and/or computer vision (depending on your strengths).
Deploy scalable and secure pipelines across Azure – leveraging services like Azure Functions, OpenAI, Vector Search, and Foundry APIs.
Work in tandem with analytics teams using dbt for transformations and model serving.
What You'll Bring:

Experience in an AI Engineering or ML Engineering role, ideally in a production-grade environment.
Strong Python coding skills, with experience building and deploying ML models.

Experience with vector databases, prompt engineering, or experience with LLMs in enterprise settings, would be highly regarded.

Ad Text:
Do you want your work to make a difference for NSW?

Working to protect the state’s environment and heritage.

 

Use your power automate and data analytical skills to contribute to the sustainable water management for the environment and communities of NSW

 

Permanent full-time role at 35 hours per week plus FlexTime
Located in Parramatta with hybrid working supported
Salary relative to experience, and ranges from $113,574 to $125,720 plus super

 

The Natural Resource Access Regulator (NRAR) enforces the NSW water laws and offers guidance and education to help water users comply. We strive to be an efficient and effective regulator that celebrates and reflects the diversity of the community we serve. Working with NRAR provides a chance to make sure water is used lawfully so that all communities and the environment get a fair share.

NRAR’s Projects and Performance team is currently seeking to appoint an Automation and Analytics Engineer to provide support to the team by designing and implementing automation and analytics solutions that drive operational efficiency and continuous improvement.

The role leverages Microsoft Power Apps, Power Automate, and Microsoft Fabric to reduce manual processes, enhance productivity, and deliver advanced analytics, including machine learning and predictive modelling. By developing user-friendly Power BI dashboards and collaborating closely with business analysts and data specialists, the role enables data-driven decision-making and strengthens NRAR’s capability to harness automation and analytics in achieving strategic outcomes.

 

About You

You are a technically adept and solutions-focused professional with demonstrated experience in leveraging Microsoft Power Platform tools including Power Apps, Power Automate, and Power BI to drive data-informed decision-making and process efficiency.

Your strong foundation in database management and data engineering collaboration enables you to resolve complex data quality issues through detailed analysis, profiling, and documentation.

You thrive in dynamic environments, confidently managing shifting priorities and evolving project requirements using agile-scrum principles. Your adaptability and time management skills ensure consistent delivery across multiple initiatives.

With hands-on experience in Microsoft Fabric, and proficiency in Python, SQL, and DAX, you bring a robust technical toolkit to support scalable data solutions. You maintain meticulous documentation practices, ensuring clarity, consistency, and accessibility across all data processes and projects.

 

Essential Requirements

Tertiary qualifications in Data Science, Computer Science, Information Systems or relevant field or equivalent experience.

 

For more information read the full Role Description:  Automation and Analytics Engineer

 

Who we are

The Department of Climate Change, Energy, the Environment and Water (DCCEEW) works to protect the state’s environment and heritage. It leads the way on climate change, driving the sustainable transition to a net zero economy, powered by affordable, reliable, and clean energy.

DCCEEW conserves and protects the state’s natural environment. It manages the NSW national park estate, including its rich and diverse biodiversity and Aboriginal cultural heritage for future generations.

DCCEEW also ensures sustainable management of water resources across the state, to support the environment, communities and industry.

We acknowledge the ongoing custodial responsibilities of the Aboriginal peoples of NSW to care for Country and water and are committed to establishing meaningful partnerships with Aboriginal peoples in the management of the environment.

NRAR enforces the NSW water laws and offers guidance and education to help water users comply. We strive to be an efficient and effective regulator that celebrates and reflects the diversity of the community we serve. Working with NRAR provides a chance to make sure water is used lawfully so that all communities and the environment get a fair share.

 

To Apply

If excited by the information above, we look forward to receiving your application, including a copy of your resume and cover letter expressing your interest and suitability for the role.

Applications close Wednesday 22 October 2025 at 11:55PM.

Should you require further information about the role please contact Aniket Prasad, Manager Performance Analytics and AI, NRAR at Aniket.prasad@nrar.nsw.gov.au.

A recruitment pool may be created for ongoing and temporary opportunities of the same role or role type that may become available over the next 18 months.

Snowflake is about empowering enterprises to achieve their full potential — and people too. With a culture that’s all in on impact, innovation, and collaboration, Snowflake is the sweet spot for building big, moving fast, and taking technology — and careers — to the next level.

There is only one Data Cloud. Snowflake’s founders started from scratch and designed a data platform built for the cloud that is effective, affordable, and accessible to all data users. But it didn’t stop there. They engineered Snowflake to power the Data Cloud, where thousands of organizations unlock the value of their data with near-unlimited scale, concurrency, and performance. This is our vision: a world with endless insights to tackle the challenges and opportunities of today and reveal the possibilities of tomorrow.

We are looking for world-class solution engineers to join our field teams whose technical skills and customer savvy will help customers understand and utilize the value of the cutting-edge data platform that we are building.

The Solution Engineer will work hand-in-hand with Sales, Product, Engineering, and Marketing. She/he will be responsible for providing the technical expertise to make Snowflake customers successful. This solution engineer will have a broad range of skills and experience ranging from data architecture to ETL/ELT, security, performance analysis, analytics, etc. He/she will have the insight to make the connection between a customer’s specific business problems and Snowflake’s solution, the customer-facing skills to communicate that connection and vision to a wide variety of technical and executive audiences, and the technical skills to be able to not only build demos and execute proof-of-concepts but also to provide consultative assistance on architecture and implementation.

The person we’re looking for shares our passion about reinventing the data platform and thrives in a dynamic environment. That means having the flexibility and willingness to jump in and get done what needs to be done to make Snowflake and our customers successful. It means keeping up to date on the ever-evolving technologies for data and analytics in order to be an authoritative resource for both Snowflake and customers. And it means working collaboratively with a broad range of people both inside and outside the company.

RESPONSIBILITIES:

Present Snowflake technology and vision to executives and technical contributors at prospects and customers

Work hands-on with prospects and customers to demonstrate and communicate the value of Snowflake technology throughout the sales cycle, from demo to proof of concept to design and implementation

Maintain a deep understanding of competitive and complementary technologies and vendors and how to position Snowflake in relation to them

Collaborate with Product Management, Engineering, and Marketing to continuously improve Snowflake’s products and marketing

MINIMUM REQUIREMENTS:

Minimum 6 years of experience working with customers in a technical pre-sales role

Outstanding skills presenting to both technical and executive audiences, whether impromptu on a whiteboard or using presentations and demos

Understanding of complete data stack and workflow, from ETL to data platform design to BI and analytics tools

Strong skills in databases, data warehouses, and data processing

Hands-on expertise with SQL and SQL analytics

STRONGLY DESIRED:

Strong Data Science/AI/ML experience across a variety of platforms

Experience and track record of success selling data and/or analytics software to enterprise customers; includes proven skills identifying key stakeholders, winning value propositions, and compelling events

Data Science knowledge and experience

Extensive knowledge of and experience with large-scale database technology (e.g. Netezza, Exadata, Teradata, Greenplum, etc.)

Software development experience with C/C++ or Java

Scripting experience with Python, Ruby, Perl, Bash

University degree in computer science, engineering, mathematics or related fields, or equivalent experience

ADDED BONUS FOR:

Experience with non-relational platforms and tools for large-scale data processing (e.g. Hadoop, HBase, etc)

Familiarity and experience with common BI and data exploration tools (e.g. Microstrategy, Business Objects, Tableau, etc)

Experience and understanding of large-scale infrastructure-as-a-service platforms (e.g. Amazon AWS, Microsoft Azure, OpenStack, etc)

Experience implementing ETL pipelines using custom and packaged tools

Experience using AWS services such as S3, Kinesis, Elastic MapReduce, Data Pipeline

Experience selling enterprise SaaS software

Snowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.

How do you want to make your impact?

Company description:



This is Symal.

Symal is a trusted partner in the building and construction industry.

We're an evolving and cohesive group of businesses offering fully integrated civil solutions across diverse sectors. Together, we believe in fostering partnerships today to create a better tomorrow.



Job description:



The role:



This is a new position for the Symal Group and a role where you can take ownership of and grow your own team as we continue to grow.

The Senior Data Scientist will lead the design, development, and implementation of enterprise-grade data solutions that drive strategic decision-making, enhance operational efficiency, and accelerate digital transformation initiatives. This role is pivotal in architecting and integrating scalable data platforms, automating data pipelines, managing master data, and delivering actionable insights through advanced analytics, Power BI, and Robotic Process Automation (RPA).

Your everyday:

This is the beginning of a new Data team therefore it will have the scope to grow and lead the team in moving forward.
This is a really solid opportunity to truly add value and this role will include however not limited to:


Application Integration (Point to Point) - Design and implement robust point-to-point integrations between enterprise applications. Ensure data consistency and reliability across systems.
Data Warehouse Automation - Automate ETL/ELT processes for the enterprise data warehouse using Azure Data Factory (ADF), Azure SQL and Data Lake.
Optimise data pipelines for performance and scalability.
Data Visualization and Analytics - Develop interactive dashboards and reports using Power BI. Enable self-service analytics for business users.
Master Data Management - Develop and maintain centralised master data repositories. Define and enforce data governance policies. Build and maintain a comprehensive enterprise data dictionary. Collaborate with stakeholders to standardise definitions.
AI Automation and RPA - Identify and automate repetitive tasks using RPA tools. Monitor and maintain RPA bots for performance.

Who are you:

7+ years of experience in data engineering, data science, or analytics roles.
Proven expertise in Microsoft Azure, Azure Data Factory, SQL, Python, and Data Warehouse modelling.
Experience with Power BI, RPA tools (e.g., Power Automate, Workato Genie, UiPath), and machine learning frameworks.
Strong understanding of enterprise systems integration and master data management.
Excellent problem-solving, communication, and stakeholder engagement skills.

At TL Consulting, we simplify modern complexity with advanced, sustainable engineering. As a proudly Australian-owned consultancy with over 15 years of experience, we empower businesses to innovate and achieve measurable outcomes through scalable, cloud-native solutions. Our 50+ consultants operate across key sectors including banking, financial services & insurance (BFSI), government, retail, education, and entertainment. This cross-industry expertise allows us to deliver customer-centric solutions that combine deep technical capability with a clear understanding of each client’s strategic vision. Our approach leverages proven, scalable blueprints tailored to your business direction—enabling accelerated outcomes, maximized ROI, and sustainable long-term adoption.

We maintain strategic partnerships with organizations that share our vision for a cloud-native future. Through our collaborations with Microsoft, GitHub, and Databricks, we ensure our capabilities stay aligned with evolving best practices. These partnerships also provide access to innovation programs, co-funding opportunities, and dedicated support—helping us accelerate time-to-value for our clients.

About the role

As the Data Solutions Architect, you will spearhead the development, growth, and strategic direction of the data engineering practice within our consultancy. Your role will focus on leading a team of data professionals, managing client engagements, and ensuring the delivery of high-quality, data-driven solutions that address client challenges. You will work closely with both internal teams and clients to help organizations leverage data for better decision-making, innovation, and growth.




KEY RESPONSIBILITIES

Practice Leadership & Development:

Define the strategic roadmap for the data engineering practice, aligning it with overall company goals.

Identify emerging trends, technologies, and opportunities to continuously evolve the practice.

Lead and orchestrate innovation initiatives aiming to mature the organisation’s data capabilities and solutions.

Develop service offerings that meet client needs, including data strategy, BI, Artificial Intelligence, advanced analytics, and data governance.

Foster a culture of innovation and continuous learning within the team.

Client Engagement & Solution Delivery:

Lead high-impact client engagements, guiding teams in the delivery of end-to-end data analytics solutions.

Provide expertise in the areas of data strategy, business intelligence, predictive analytics, and data management.

Collaborate with clients to understand business objectives and design tailored data-driven solutions.

Ensure projects are delivered on time, within scope, and meet quality standards.

Build and maintain strong, long-term relationships with key clients to ensure repeat business.

Team Leadership & Development:

Manage and mentor a team of data engineers and analysts, promoting collaboration and career growth.

Recruit, retain, and develop talent within the data engineering team.

Conduct regular performance reviews and provide feedback to enhance team capabilities.

Foster a collaborative environment that encourages innovation and best practices.

Business Development & Sales Support:

Support business development efforts by working closely with the sales team to identify and pursue new opportunities.

Lead and contribute to proposal writing, client presentations, and pre-sales activities.

Act as a subject matter expert (SME) during client discussions, showcasing the value of data solutions in tackling business problems.

Identify potential partnerships and collaborations that can enhance the practice’s offerings.

Thought Leadership:

Serve as the face of the data engineering practice in industry forums, conferences, and events.

Publish white papers, blogs, and case studies to showcase the consultancy’s capabilities and success stories.

Stay abreast of industry trends, emerging tools, and methodologies, sharing insights with clients and internal teams.


SKILLS & EXPERIENCE

Required Skills and Qualifications:

Education: Bachelor’s degree in engineering, Computer Science, or a related field. Master’s degree or MBA preferred.

Experience:

10+ years of experience in data analytics, business intelligence, or related data domains.

5+ years of experience in a consulting or professional services environment.

Proven experience in leading data engineering teams and delivering client-focused solutions.

Technical Skills:

Expertise in data analytics tools and platforms (e.g., SQL, Python, R, Apache Spark, Tableau, Power BI).

Expertise in Azure services and analytics platforms such as Databricks, Synapse and MS Fabric.

Knowledge of other cloud platforms (e.g. AWS, Google Cloud) is a plus.

Familiar with DMBOK and/or TOGAF frameworks.

Expertise with data lake modelling such as Kimball (Star Schema) and Data Vault modelling.

Strong understanding of machine learning, predictive analytics, and data visualization techniques.

Soft Skills:

Strong clients focus and ensure effective relationships are in place with key client stakeholders to deliver that service.

Excellent client relationship management skills with the ability to explain complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Strong stakeholder management skills interfacing with diverse stakeholders. i.e., General Manager, Head of Architecture, Solution Architecture.

Solid experience in relationship management, conflict resolution, influencing and negotiation.

Must be able to work independently but also lead Consulting engagements in a highly matrixed environment (especially for short-term engagements).

Uphold and exceed enterprise-grade compliance standards, such as SOC2, ensuring our products are secure and reliable.

Not only do you have impressive problem-solving skills, we also value your leadership mindset and ability to proactively take charge in a fast moving environment. 

To be successful you must demonstrate the following:

Strong background in Node.js development is a must. Python is a plus.

Strong background in LangChain, AI Agent frameworks, and ability to apply these advanced AI solutions, OR you’re passionate about learning this (we will train you!)

Strong experience in building secure, scalable APIs.

Strong understanding of cloud environments (Azure, AWS, GCP)

Impressive problem solving / analytical skills

Impeccable attention to detail and integrity in your work ethic, you follow-through on doing what you said you’ll do.

Bonus

Experience with orchestration applications like Flowise 

Proficiency in CICD, Kubernetes and containerization technologies
